#. <title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="en"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pārājikakaṇḍa"
msgstr "Monks’ Expulsion"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Catut­tha­pā­rāji­ka­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "4. The fourth training rule"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs0.5"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pj.4"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pj.4.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pj.4.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.151"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.87"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.534"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭā­gāra­sālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī in the hall with the peaked "
"roof in the Great Wood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā sandiṭṭhā sambhattā bhikkhū vaggumudāya "
"nadiyā tīre vassaṃ upagacchiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"At that time a number of monks who were friends had entered the rains "
"residence on the banks of the river Vaggumudā."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena vajjī dubbhikkhā hoti dvīhitikā setaṭṭhikā "
"salākāvuttā,"
msgstr ""
"Just then Vajjī was short of food and afflicted with hunger, with crops "
"blighted and turned to straw,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid "na sukarā uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ."
msgstr "and it was not easy to get by on almsfood."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—“etarahi kho vajjī dubbhikkhā dvīhitikā "
"setaṭṭhikā salākāvuttā, na sukarā uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ."
msgstr "The monks considered the difficult circumstances, and they thought, "

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid ""
"Kena nu kho mayaṃ upāyena samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ "
"vaseyyāma,"
msgstr "“How can we remain united and in harmony, have a comfortable rains,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid "na ca piṇḍakena kilameyyāmā”ti?"
msgstr "and get almsfood without problems?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.535"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid "Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Some said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid "“handa mayaṃ, āvuso, gihīnaṃ kammantaṃ adhiṭṭhema,"
msgstr "“We could work for the lay people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid "evaṃ te amhākaṃ dātuṃ maññissanti."
msgstr "and they’ll give something in return."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid "Evaṃ mayaṃ samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasissāma,"
msgstr ""
"In this way we’ll be united and in harmony, and we’ll spend the rains in "
"comfort"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.12"
msgid "na ca piṇḍakena kilamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "and have no problems getting almsfood.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.536"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.13"
msgid "Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Some said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.14"
msgid "“alaṃ, āvuso, kiṃ gihīnaṃ kammantaṃ adhiṭṭhitena."
msgstr "“There’s no need to work for the lay people."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.152"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.15"
msgid "Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, gihīnaṃ dūteyyaṃ harāma,"
msgstr "Let’s instead take messages for them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.16"
msgid "evaṃ te amhākaṃ dātuṃ maññissanti."
msgstr "and they’ll give something in return."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.17"
msgid "Evaṃ mayaṃ samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasissāma,"
msgstr ""
"In this way we’ll be united and in harmony, and we’ll spend the rains in "
"comfort"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.18"
msgid "na ca piṇḍakena kilamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "and have no problems getting almsfood.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.537"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.19"
msgid "Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Some said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.20"
msgid "“alaṃ, āvuso, kiṃ gihīnaṃ kammantaṃ adhiṭṭhitena."
msgstr "“There’s no need to work for the lay people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.21"
msgid "Kiṃ gihīnaṃ dūteyyaṃ haṭena."
msgstr "nor to take messages for them."

#. VAR: bhāsissāma → bhāsāma (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.22"
msgid ""
"Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttari­manus­sa­dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ "
"bhāsissāma—"
msgstr ""
"Let’s instead praise one another’s superhuman qualities to the lay people:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.23"
msgid "‘asuko bhikkhu paṭhamassa jhānassa lābhī,"
msgstr "‘Such a monk has the first absorption,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.24"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu dutiyassa jhānassa lābhī,"
msgstr "such a monk the second absorption,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.25"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu tatiyassa jhānassa lābhī,"
msgstr "such a monk the third,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.26"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu catutthassa jhānassa lābhī,"
msgstr "such a monk the fourth;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.27"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu sotāpanno,"
msgstr "such a monk is a stream-enterer,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.28"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu sakadāgāmī,"
msgstr "such a monk a once-returner,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.29"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu anāgāmī,"
msgstr "such a non-returner,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.30"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu arahā,"
msgstr "such a perfected one;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.31"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu tevijjo,"
msgstr "such a monk has the three true insights,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.32"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu chaḷabhiñño’ti."
msgstr "and such the six direct knowledges.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.33"
msgid "Evaṃ te amhākaṃ dātuṃ maññissanti."
msgstr "Then they’ll give to us."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.88"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.34"
msgid "Evaṃ mayaṃ samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasissāma,"
msgstr ""
"In this way we’ll be united and in harmony, and we’ll spend the rains in "
"comfort"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.35"
msgid "na ca piṇḍakena kilamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "and have no problems getting almsfood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.36"
msgid ""
"“Esoyeva kho, āvuso, seyyo yo amhākaṃ gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttari­manus­sa­"
"dhammassa vaṇṇo bhāsito”ti."
msgstr ""
"Indeed, this is the better way, that we praise one another’s superhuman "
"qualities to the lay people.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.538"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.37"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttari­manus­sa­dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ "
"bhāsiṃsu—"
msgstr ""
"Then those monks praised one another’s superhuman qualities to the lay "
"people:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.38"
msgid "“asuko bhikkhu paṭhamassa jhānassa lābhī … pe …"
msgstr "“Such a monk has the first absorption …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.39"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu chaḷabhiñño”ti."
msgstr "such a monk has the six direct knowledges.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.40"
msgid "Atha kho te manussā—"
msgstr "And those people thought,"

#. VAR: yesaṃ no → vata no (c1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.41"
msgid ""
"“lābhā vata no, suladdhaṃ vata no, yesaṃ no evarūpā bhikkhū vassaṃ upagatā;"
msgstr ""
"“We’re fortunate that such monks have come to us for the rains residence."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.153"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.42"
msgid ""
"na vata no ito pubbe evarūpā bhikkhū vassaṃ upagatā yathayime bhikkhū "
"sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā”ti,"
msgstr ""
"Such monks as these, who are virtuous and of good character, have never "
"before entered the rains residence with us.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.43"
msgid ""
"te na tādisāni bhojanāni attanā paribhuñjanti mātāpitūnaṃ denti puttadārassa "
"denti dāsakam­ma­ka­ra­porisassa denti mittāmaccānaṃ denti ñāti­sālo­hi­tā­"
"naṃ denti, yādisāni bhikkhūnaṃ denti."
msgstr ""
"And they gave such food and drink to those monks that they did not even eat "
"and drink themselves, or give to their parents, to their wives and children, "
"to their slaves, servants, and workers, to their friends and companions, or "
"to their relatives."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.44"
msgid ""
"Te na tādisāni khādanīyāni sāyanīyāni pānāni attanā khādanti sāyanti pivanti "
"mātāpitūnaṃ denti puttadārassa denti dāsakam­ma­ka­ra­porisassa denti "
"mittāmaccānaṃ denti ñāti­sālo­hi­tā­naṃ denti, yādisāni bhikkhūnaṃ denti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.1.45"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū vaṇṇavā ahesuṃ pīṇindriyā pasan­na­mukha­vaṇṇā "
"vippa­sanna­chavi­vaṇṇā."
msgstr ""
"In this way those monks were handsome, with rounded features, bright faces, "
"and clear skin."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pj.4.1.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.539"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid ""
"Āciṇṇaṃ kho panetaṃ vassaṃ­vuṭṭhā­naṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamituṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now it was the custom for monks who had finished keeping the rains residence "
"to go to see the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū vassaṃvuṭṭhā temāsaccayena senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā "
"pattacīvaraṃ ādāya yena vesālī tena pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"So when the rainy-season residence was completed and the three months had "
"elapsed, those monks put their dwellings in order, took their bowls and "
"robes, and departed for Vesālī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid ""
"Anupubbena yena vesālī mahāvanaṃ kūṭāgārasālā yena bhagavā "
"tenu­pasaṅka­miṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"When they eventually arrived at Vesālī, they went to the hall with the "
"peaked roof in the Great Wood. There they approached the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.540"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.154"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena disāsu vassaṃvuṭṭhā bhikkhū kisā honti lūkhā dubbaṇṇā "
"uppaṇḍup­paṇḍuka­jātā dhama­ni­san­tha­ta­gattā;"
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks who had completed the rainy-season residence in that "
"region were thin, haggard, and pale, their veins protruding all over their "
"limbs."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid ""
"vaggu­mudā­tīriyā pana bhikkhū vaṇṇavā honti pīṇindriyā pasan­na­mukha­vaṇṇā "
"vippa­sanna­chavi­vaṇṇā."
msgstr ""
"But the monks from the banks of the Vaggumudā were handsome, with rounded "
"features, bright faces, and clear skin."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid ""
"Āciṇṇaṃ kho panetaṃ buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ āgantukehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ "
"paṭisammodituṃ."
msgstr "It is the custom for Buddhas to greet newly arrived monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā vaggu­mudā­tīriye bhikkhū etadavoca—"
msgstr "and so the Master said to them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid ""
"“kacci, bhikkhave, khamanīyaṃ kacci yāpanīyaṃ kacci samaggā sammodamānā "
"avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasittha,"
msgstr ""
"“I hope you’re keeping well, monks, I hope you’re comfortable; I hope you "
"spent the rains at ease, in concord and harmony, without dispute,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid "na ca piṇḍakena kilamitthā”ti?"
msgstr "and that you had no trouble getting almsfood?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid "“Khamanīyaṃ, bhagavā, yāpanīyaṃ, bhagavā."
msgstr "“We’re keeping well, Master, we’re comfortable;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.12"
msgid ""
"Samaggā ca mayaṃ, bhante, sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasimhā,"
msgstr "we spent the rains at ease, in concord and harmony, without dispute,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.13"
msgid "na ca piṇḍakena kilamimhā”ti."
msgstr "and we had no trouble getting almsfood.”"

#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.89"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.14"
msgid "Jānantāpi tathāgatā pucchanti, jānantāpi na pucchanti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Buddhas sometimes ask knowing, and knowing sometimes do not ask; they ask "
"knowing the right time to ask, and they ask knowing the right time not to "
"ask. Buddhas ask when it is beneficial, not when it is unbeneficial; in "
"regard to what is unbeneficial, the Buddhas have destroyed the bridge."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.15"
msgid "dvīhākārehi buddhā bhagavanto bhikkhū paṭipucchanti—"
msgstr "Buddhas question the monks for two reasons:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.16"
msgid "“dhammaṃ vā desessāma, sāvakānaṃ vā sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmā”ti."
msgstr "to give a teaching or to lay down a training rule."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.541"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.17"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā vaggu­mudā­tīriye bhikkhū etadavoca—"
msgstr "And the Master said to those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.18"
msgid ""
"“yathā kathaṃ pana tumhe, bhikkhave, samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā "
"phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasittha na ca piṇḍakena kilamitthā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“In what way, monks, did you spend the rains at ease, without having any "
"trouble getting almsfood?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.19"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "Then those monks told the Master."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.20"
msgid "“Kacci pana vo, bhikkhave, bhūtan”ti?"
msgstr "“But had you really achieved those superhuman qualities?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.21"
msgid "“Abhūtaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.22"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.155"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.23"
msgid ""
"“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisā, ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ "
"akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“It’s unsuitable, foolish men, it’s not proper, it’s not fitting for an "
"ascetic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.24"
msgid ""
"Kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, udarassa kāraṇā gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa "
"uttari­manus­sa­dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissatha."
msgstr ""
"How can you for the sake of your stomachs praise one another’s superhuman "
"qualities to lay people?"

#. VAR: govikantanena → govikattanena (bj, pts1, mr) | govikatthanena (si)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.25"
msgid ""
"Varaṃ tumhehi, moghapurisā, tiṇhena govikantanena kucchi parikanto, na tveva "
"udarassa kāraṇā gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttari­manus­sa­dhammassa vaṇṇo bhāsito."
msgstr ""
"It would be better for your bellies to be cut open with a sharp butcher’s "
"knife than for you to praise one another’s superhuman qualities to lay "
"people."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.26"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.27"
msgid ""
"Tatonidānañhi, moghapurisā, maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ,"
msgstr ""
"Because for that reason you might die or experience death-like suffering,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.28"
msgid ""
"na tveva tappaccayā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ "
"nirayaṃ upapajjeyya."
msgstr "but you wouldn’t because of that be reborn in a bad destination."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.29"
msgid ""
"Itonidānañca kho, moghapurisā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ "
"vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya."
msgstr "But for <em>this</em> reason you might."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.30"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.2.31"
msgid "vigarahitvā dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "After criticizing them and giving a teaching, he addressed the monks:"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pj.4.1.3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.542"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, mahācorā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, there are these five great gangsters to be found in the world."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa mahācorassa evaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "A great gangster thinks like this:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.4"
msgid ""
"‘kudāssu nāmāhaṃ satena vā sahassena vā parivuto gāmani­gama­rāja­dhānīsu "
"āhiṇḍissāmi"
msgstr ""
"‘Oh when will I, with a following of a hundred or a thousand men, wander "
"among villages, towns, and royal capitals,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.5"
msgid "hananto ghātento"
msgstr "killing and making others kill,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.6"
msgid "chindanto chedāpento"
msgstr "destroying and making others destroy,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.7"
msgid "pacanto pācento’ti."
msgstr "tormenting and making others torment?’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.8"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena satena vā sahassena vā parivuto gāmani­gama­rāja­dhānīsu "
"āhiṇḍati hananto ghātento chindanto chedāpento pacanto pācento."
msgstr "Then after some time, he does just that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.9"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekaccassa pāpabhikkhuno evaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "Just so, monks, a bad monk thinks like this:"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.156"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.10"
msgid ""
"‘kudāssu nāmāhaṃ satena vā sahassena vā parivuto gāmani­gama­rāja­dhānīsu "
"cārikaṃ carissāmi sakkato garukato mānito pūjito apacito gahaṭ­ṭhā­nañ­ceva "
"pabbajitānañca,"
msgstr ""
"‘Oh when will I, with a following of a hundred or a thousand people, go "
"wandering among villages, towns, and royal capitals; be honored, respected, "
"and revered by both lay people and those gone forth;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.11"
msgid ""
"lābhī "
"cīvara­piṇḍa­pāta­se­nāsa­na­gilā­nappac­caya­bhesaj­ja­parik­khā­rā­nan’ti."
msgstr "and obtain robe-cloth, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines?’"

#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.90"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.12"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena satena vā sahassena vā parivuto gāmani­gama­rāja­dhānīsu "
"cārikaṃ carati sakkato garukato mānito pūjito apacito gahaṭ­ṭhā­nañ­ceva "
"pabbajitānañca, lābhī "
"cīvara­piṇḍa­pāta­se­nāsa­na­gilā­nappac­caya­bhesaj­ja­parik­khā­rā­naṃ."
msgstr "Then after some time, he does just that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.13"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo mahācoro santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "This is the first great gangster to be found in the world."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.14"
msgid "(1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.543"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.15"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco pāpabhikkhu tathā­gatap­pa­vedi­taṃ "
"dhammavinayaṃ pariyāpuṇitvā attano dahati."
msgstr ""
"Again, a bad monk learns the Teaching and training proclaimed by the Buddha "
"and takes it as his own."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.16"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo mahācoro santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "This is the second great gangster to be found in the world."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.17"
msgid "(2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.544"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.18"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco pāpabhikkhu suddhaṃ brahmacāriṃ "
"parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carantaṃ amūlakena abrahma­cari­yena anuddhaṃseti."
msgstr ""
"Again, a bad monk groundlessly accuses someone who lives the spiritual life "
"in purity of not abstaining from sexuality."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.19"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo mahācoro santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "This is the third great gangster to be found in the world."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.20"
msgid "(3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.545"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.21"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco pāpabhikkhu yāni tāni saṃghassa "
"garubhaṇḍāni garu­parik­khā­rāni, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Again, a bad monk takes valuable goods and equipment belonging to the Order—"

#. I have rendered <i lang="pli">muñja</i>-reed and <i lang="pli">pabbaja</i>-reed with the single word “reed.” I am not aware that these two types of reed can be distinguished in English.
#. VAR: bibbohanaṃ → bimbohanaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: parasu → pharasu (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.22"
msgid ""
"ārāmo ārāmavatthu vihāro vihāravatthu mañco pīṭhaṃ bhisi bibbohanaṃ "
"lohakumbhī lohabhāṇakaṃ lohavārako lohakaṭāhaṃ vāsi parasu kuṭhārī kudālo "
"nikhādanaṃ valli veḷu muñjaṃ pabbajaṃ tiṇaṃ mattikā dārubhaṇḍaṃ "
"mattikābhaṇḍaṃ,"
msgstr ""
"a monastery, the land of a monastery, a dwelling, the land of a dwelling, a "
"bed, a bench, a cushion, a pillow, a metal vessel, a metal jar, a metal pot, "
"a metal receptacle, an adz, a hatchet, an ax, a spade, a chisel, a creeper, "
"bamboo, reed, grass, clay, wooden articles, earthenware articles—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.23"
msgid "tehi gihiṃ saṅgaṇhāti upalāpeti."
msgstr "and uses them to win over and create a following among lay people."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.24"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho mahācoro santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "This is the fourth great gangster to be found in the world."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.25"
msgid "(4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.157"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.546"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.26"
msgid ""
"Sadevake, bhikkhave, loke samārake sabrahmake ­sassama­ṇab­rāhma­ṇiyā pajāya "
"sade­va­manus­sāya ayaṃ aggo mahācoro yo asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttari­manus­sa­"
"dhammaṃ ullapati."
msgstr ""
"But in this world with its gods, its lords of death, and its supreme beings, "
"in this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans, this "
"is the greatest gangster: he who untruthfully and groundlessly boasts about "
"a superhuman quality."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.27"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.28"
msgid "Theyyāya vo, bhikkhave, raṭṭhapiṇḍo bhutto”ti."
msgstr "Monks, you’ve eaten the country’s almsfood by theft.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.29"
msgid "(5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.547"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.30"
msgid "Aññathā santamattānaṃ,"
msgstr "Whoever should declare himself"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.31"
msgid "aññathā yo pavedaye;"
msgstr "to be other than he truly is,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.32"
msgid "Nikacca kitavasseva,"
msgstr "Has eaten this by theft,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.33"
msgid "bhuttaṃ theyyena tassa taṃ."
msgstr "like a cheater who has deceived."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.548"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.34"
msgid "Kāsāvakaṇṭhā bahavo,"
msgstr "Many ocher-necks of bad qualities,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.35"
msgid "pāpadhammā asaññatā;"
msgstr "uncontrolled and wicked—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.36"
msgid "Pāpā pāpehi kammehi,"
msgstr "By their wicked deeds,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.37"
msgid "nirayaṃ te upapajjare."
msgstr "they are reborn in hell."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.549"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.38"
msgid "Seyyo ayoguḷo bhutto,"
msgstr "It is better to eat an iron ball,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.39"
msgid "tatto aggisikhūpamo;"
msgstr "heated, like a burning flame,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.40"
msgid "Yañce bhuñjeyya dussīlo,"
msgstr "Than for the immoral and uncontrolled"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.41"
msgid "raṭṭhapiṇḍaṃ asaññatoti."
msgstr "to eat the country’s alms."

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.550"></a> 
#. VAR: bhagavā → bhagavā te (c1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.42"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā vaggu­mudā­tīriye bhikkhū aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā "
"dubbharatāya dupposatāya … pe …"
msgstr ""
"After criticizing the monks from the banks of the Vaggumudā in various ways "
"for being difficult to maintain, difficult to support …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.43"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "“… And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.43a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.551"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.158"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.44"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu anabhijānaṃ uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ attupanāyikaṃ "
"ala­mariya­ñāṇadas­sanaṃ samudācareyya—"
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk falsely claims for himself a superhuman quality, knowledge and "
"vision worthy of the noble ones, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.45"
msgid "‘iti jānāmi iti passāmī’ti,"
msgstr "“This I know, this I see,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.46"
msgid ""
"tato aparena samayena sama­nug­gāhīya­māno vā asama­nug­gāhīya­māno vā "
"āpanno visuddhāpekkho evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr ""
"but after some time—whether questioned or not, but having committed the "
"offense and desiring purification—should say:"

#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.91"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.47"
msgid "‘ajānamevaṃ, āvuso, avacaṃ jānāmi,"
msgstr "“Not knowing I said that I know,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.48"
msgid "apassaṃ passāmi."
msgstr "not seeing that I see;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.49"
msgid "Tucchaṃ musā vilapin’ti,"
msgstr "what I said was empty and false,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.50"
msgid "ayampi pārājiko hoti asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "he too is expelled and excluded from the community.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.552"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs1.3.51"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pj.4.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.553"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū adiṭṭhe diṭṭhasaññino apatte "
"pattasaññino anadhigate adhi­gata­saññino asacchikate ­sacchi­kata­saññino "
"adhimānena aññaṃ byākariṃsu."
msgstr ""
"At one time a number of monks, thinking they had seen what they had not, "
"attained what they had not, achieved what they had not, realized what they "
"had not, declared final knowledge because of overestimation."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.2"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ aparena samayena rāgāyapi cittaṃ namati dosāyapi cittaṃ namati "
"mohāyapi cittaṃ namati."
msgstr ""
"After some time, their minds inclined to sensual desire, ill-will, and "
"confusion."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "Tesaṃ kukkuccaṃ ahosi—"
msgstr "They became remorseful, thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "“bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ."
msgstr "“The Master has laid down a training rule;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.5"
msgid ""
"Mayañcamha adiṭṭhe diṭṭhasaññino apatte pattasaññino anadhigate adhi­gata­"
"saññino asacchikate ­sacchi­kata­saññino, adhimānena aññaṃ byākarimhā."
msgstr "yet we declared final knowledge because of overestimation."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "Kacci nu kho mayaṃ pārājikaṃ āpattiṃ āpannā”ti?"
msgstr "Could it be that we’ve committed an offense entailing expulsion?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Te āyasmato ānandassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told Venerable Ānanda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "Āyasmā ānando bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "who told the Master."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.159"></a> 
#. VAR: ānanda → honti te ānanda (bj) | honti yevānanda (s1) | hontiyevānanda (s2, s3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.9"
msgid ""
"“Honti ye te, ānanda, bhikkhū adiṭṭhe diṭṭhasaññino apatte pattasaññino "
"anadhigate adhi­gata­saññino asacchikate ­sacchi­kata­saññino adhimānena "
"aññaṃ byākaronti."
msgstr ""
"He said, “Ānanda, these monks declared final knowledge because of "
"overestimation, thinking they had seen what they had not, attained what they "
"had not, achieved what they had not, realized what they had not,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Tañca kho etaṃ abbohārikan”ti."
msgstr "but this is negligible."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.554"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.11a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.555"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: attupanāyikaṃ → attūpanāyikaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.12"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu anabhijānaṃ uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ attupanāyikaṃ "
"ala­mariya­ñāṇadas­sanaṃ samudācareyya—"
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk falsely claims for himself a superhuman quality, knowledge and "
"vision worthy of the noble ones, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "‘iti jānāmi iti passāmī’ti,"
msgstr "“This I know, this I see,”"

#. VAR: sama­nug­gāhīya­māno → sama­nug­gāhiya­māno (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: asama­nug­gāhīya­māno → asama­nug­gāhiya­māno (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.14"
msgid ""
"tato aparena samayena sama­nug­gāhīya­māno vā asama­nug­gāhīya­māno vā "
"āpanno visuddhāpekkho evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr ""
"but after some time—whether he is questioned or not, but having committed "
"the offense and desiring purification—should say:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "‘ajānamevaṃ, āvuso, avacaṃ jānāmi,"
msgstr "“Not knowing I said that I know,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "apassaṃ passāmi."
msgstr "not seeing that I see;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "Tucchaṃ musā vilapin’ti,"
msgstr "what I said was empty and false,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "aññatra adhimānā,"
msgstr "unless it is due to overestimation,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "ayampi pārājiko hoti asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "he too is expelled and excluded from the community.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs2.20"
msgid "(<em>4</em>:<strong>4</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pj.4.3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.556"></a> <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span> <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.557"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.6"
msgid "Anabhijānanti"
msgstr "Falsely:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.7"
msgid ""
"asantaṃ abhūtaṃ asaṃvijjamānaṃ ajānanto apassanto attani kusalaṃ dhammaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"although a certain wholesome quality is non-existent in himself, not real, "
"not to be found, and he does not see it or know it,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.8"
msgid "atthi me kusalo dhammoti."
msgstr "he says, “I have this wholesome quality.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.558"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.9"
msgid "Uttari­manus­sa­dhammo nāma"
msgstr "A superhuman quality:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: vimokkho → vimokkhaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.10"
msgid ""
"jhānaṃ vimokkho samādhi samāpatti ñāṇadassanaṃ maggabhāvanā phala­sacchi­"
"kiriyā kilesappahānaṃ vinīvaraṇatā cittassa suññāgāre abhirati."
msgstr ""
"absorption, release, stillness, attainment, knowledge and vision, "
"development of the path, realization of the fruits, abandoning the "
"defilements, a mind without hindrances, delighting in empty dwellings."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.559"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.11"
msgid "Attupanāyikanti"
msgstr "For himself:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.12"
msgid ""
"te vā kusale dhamme attani upaneti attānaṃ vā tesu kusalesu dhammesu upaneti."
msgstr ""
"either he presents those good qualities as in himself, or he presents "
"himself as among those good qualities."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.560"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.13"
msgid "Ñāṇanti"
msgstr "Knowledge:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.14"
msgid "tisso vijjā."
msgstr "the three true insights."

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.15"
msgid "Dassananti"
msgstr "Vision:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.16"
msgid "yaṃ ñāṇaṃ taṃ dassanaṃ, yaṃ dassanaṃ taṃ ñāṇaṃ."
msgstr "knowledge and vision are equivalent."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.92"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.561"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.17"
msgid "Samudācareyyāti"
msgstr "Claims:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.18"
msgid "āroceyya itthiyā vā purisassa vā gahaṭṭhassa vā pabbajitassa vā."
msgstr "announces to a woman or a man, to a lay person or one gone forth."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.562"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.19"
msgid "Iti jānāmi iti passāmīti"
msgstr "This I know, this I see:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.20"
msgid "jānāmahaṃ ete dhamme,"
msgstr "“I know these qualities/"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.160"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.21"
msgid "passāmahaṃ ete dhamme atthi ca ete dhammā mayi,"
msgstr "I see these qualities/these qualities are found in me"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.22"
msgid "ahañca etesu dhammesu sandissāmīti."
msgstr "and I conform to them.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.563"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.23"
msgid "Tato aparena samayenāti"
msgstr "After some time:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.24"
msgid ""
"yasmiṃ khaṇe samudāciṇṇaṃ hoti taṃ khaṇaṃ taṃ layaṃ taṃ muhuttaṃ vītivatte."
msgstr "the moment, the second, the instant after he has made the claim."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.564"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.25"
msgid "Sama­nug­gāhīya­mānoti"
msgstr "He is questioned:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.26"
msgid "yaṃ vatthu paṭiññātaṃ hoti tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ sama­nug­gāhīya­māno—"
msgstr "he is questioned in regard to what he has admitted:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.27"
msgid "“kinte adhigataṃ,"
msgstr "“What did you attain?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.28"
msgid "kinti te adhigataṃ,"
msgstr "How did you attain it?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.29"
msgid "kadā te adhigataṃ,"
msgstr "When did you attain it?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.30"
msgid "kattha te adhigataṃ,"
msgstr "Where did you attain it?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.31"
msgid "katame te kilesā pahīnā,"
msgstr "Which defilements did you abandon?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.32"
msgid "katamesaṃ tvaṃ dhammānaṃ lābhī”ti."
msgstr "Which qualities did you gain?”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.565"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.33"
msgid "Asama­nug­gāhīya­mānoti"
msgstr "Not:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.34"
msgid "na kenaci vuccamāno."
msgstr "he is not spoken to by anyone."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.566"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.35"
msgid "Āpannoti"
msgstr "Having committed the offense:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.36"
msgid ""
"pāpiccho icchāpakato asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ ullapitvā "
"pārājikaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno hoti."
msgstr ""
"having bad desires, overcome by desire, claiming a non-existent, unreal "
"superhuman quality, he has committed an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.567"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.37"
msgid "Visuddhāpekkhoti"
msgstr "Desiring purification:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.38"
msgid ""
"gihī vā hotukāmo upāsako vā hotukāmo ārāmiko vā hotukāmo sāmaṇero vā "
"hotukāmo."
msgstr ""
"he desires to be a lay person, a lay follower, a monastery attendant, or a "
"novice monk."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.568"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.39"
msgid "Ajānamevaṃ, āvuso, avacaṃ—jānāmi, apassaṃ passāmīti"
msgstr "Not knowing I said that I know, not seeing that I see:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.40"
msgid "nāhaṃ ete dhamme jānāmi,"
msgstr "“I don’t know these qualities/"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.41"
msgid "nāhaṃ ete dhamme passāmi,"
msgstr "I don’t see these qualities/"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.42"
msgid "natthi ca ete dhammā mayi,"
msgstr "these qualities aren’t found in me"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.43"
msgid "na cāhaṃ etesu dhammesu sandissāmīti."
msgstr "and I don’t conform to them.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.569"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.44"
msgid "Tucchaṃ musā vilapinti"
msgstr "What I said was empty and false:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.45"
msgid "tucchakaṃ mayā bhaṇitaṃ,"
msgstr "what I said was empty;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.46"
msgid "musā mayā bhaṇitaṃ,"
msgstr "what I said was false;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.47"
msgid "abhūtaṃ mayā bhaṇitaṃ,"
msgstr "what I said was unreal;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.48"
msgid "ajānantena mayā bhaṇitaṃ."
msgstr "I said it without knowing."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.570"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.49"
msgid "Aññatra adhimānāti"
msgstr "Unless it is due to overestimation:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.50"
msgid "ṭhapetvā adhimānaṃ."
msgstr "except if it is overestimation."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.571"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.51"
msgid "Ayampīti"
msgstr "He too:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.52"
msgid "purime upādāya vuccati."
msgstr ""
"this is said with reference to the preceding offenses entailing expulsion."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.572"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.53"
msgid "Pārājiko hotīti"
msgstr "Is expelled:"

#. </span>
#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.161"></a>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.54"
msgid "seyyathāpi nāma tālo mattha­kac­chinno abhabbo puna virūḷhiyā;"
msgstr ""
"just as a palm tree with its crown cut off is incapable of further growth, "

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.55"
msgid ""
"evameva bhikkhu pāpiccho icchāpakato asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ "
"ullapitvā assamaṇo hoti asakyaputtiyo."
msgstr ""
"so too a monk with bad desires, overcome by desire, who has claimed a non-"
"existent, unreal superhuman quality, is not an ascetic, not a son of the "
"Sakyan—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.56"
msgid "Tena vuccati—"
msgstr "therefore it is said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.57"
msgid "“pārājiko hotī”ti."
msgstr "“he is expelled.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.573"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.58"
msgid "Asaṃvāsoti"
msgstr "Excluded from the community:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.59"
msgid "saṃvāso nāma"
msgstr "Community:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.60"
msgid "ekakammaṃ ekuddeso samasikkhatā—"
msgstr "common procedures, the same recital, the same training—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.61"
msgid "eso saṃvāso nāma."
msgstr "this is called “community.”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.62"
msgid "So tena saddhiṃ natthi."
msgstr "He does not take part in this—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.63"
msgid "Tena vuccati—"
msgstr "therefore it is called"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs3.64"
msgid "“asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "“excluded from the community.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Summary"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pj.4.4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pj.4.4.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.574"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.1"
msgid "Uttari­manus­sa­dhammo nāma"
msgstr "A superhuman quality:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.2"
msgid ""
"jhānaṃ vimokkho samādhi samāpatti ñāṇadassanaṃ maggabhāvanā phala­sacchi­"
"kiriyā kilesappahānaṃ vinīvaraṇatā cittassa suññāgāre abhirati."
msgstr ""
"absorption, release, stillness, attainment, knowledge and vision, "
"development of the path, realization of the fruits, abandoning the "
"defilements, a mind without hindrances, delighting in empty dwellings."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.2a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.575"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.3"
msgid "Jhānanti"
msgstr "Absorption:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.4"
msgid "paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ"
msgstr "the first absorption,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.5"
msgid "dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ"
msgstr "the second absorption,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.6"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ"
msgstr "the third absorption,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.7"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ."
msgstr "the fourth absorption."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.576"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.8"
msgid "Vimokkhoti"
msgstr "Release:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.9"
msgid "suññato vimokkho"
msgstr "emptiness release,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.10"
msgid "animitto vimokkho"
msgstr "signless release,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.11"
msgid "appaṇihito vimokkho."
msgstr "desireless release."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.93"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.577"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.12"
msgid "Samādhīti"
msgstr "Stillness:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.13"
msgid "suññato samādhi"
msgstr "emptiness stillness,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.14"
msgid "animitto samādhi"
msgstr "signless stillness,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.15"
msgid "appaṇihito samādhi."
msgstr "desireless stillness."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.578"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.16"
msgid "Samāpattīti"
msgstr "Attainment:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.17"
msgid "suññatā samāpatti"
msgstr "emptiness attainment,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.18"
msgid "animittā samāpatti"
msgstr "signless attainment,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.19"
msgid "appaṇihitā samāpatti."
msgstr "desireless attainment."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="46"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.579"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.20"
msgid "Ñāṇadassananti"
msgstr "Knowledge and vision:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.21"
msgid "tisso vijjā."
msgstr "the three true insights."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="47"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.580"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.22"
msgid "Maggabhāvanāti"
msgstr "Development of the path:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.23"
msgid "cattāro satipaṭṭhānā,"
msgstr "the four applications of mindfulness,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.24"
msgid "cattāro sammappadhānā,"
msgstr "the four right efforts,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.162"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.25"
msgid "cattāro iddhipādā,"
msgstr "the four bases of supernormal power,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.26"
msgid "pañcindriyāni,"
msgstr "the five spiritual faculties,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.27"
msgid "pañca balāni,"
msgstr "the five spiritual powers,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.28"
msgid "satta bojjhaṅgā,"
msgstr "the seven factors of awakening,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.29"
msgid "ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo."
msgstr "the noble eightfold path."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="48"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.581"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.30"
msgid "Phala­sacchi­kiriyāti"
msgstr "Realization of the fruits:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.31"
msgid "sotā­patti­phalassa sacchikiriyā,"
msgstr "realization of the fruit of stream-entry,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.32"
msgid "sakadā­gāmi­phalassa sacchikiriyā,"
msgstr "realization of the fruit of once-returning,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.33"
msgid "anāgā­mi­phalassa sacchikiriyā,"
msgstr "realization of the fruit of non-returning,"

#. VAR: arahattassa → arahat­ta­phalassa (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.34"
msgid "arahattassa sacchikiriyā."
msgstr "realization of perfection."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="49"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.582"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.35"
msgid "Kilesappahānanti"
msgstr "Abandoning the defilements:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.36"
msgid "rāgassa pahānaṃ"
msgstr "the abandoning of sensual desire,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.37"
msgid "dosassa pahānaṃ"
msgstr "the abandoning of ill-will,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.38"
msgid "mohassa pahānaṃ."
msgstr "the abandoning of confusion."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="50"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.583"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.39"
msgid "Vinīvaraṇatā cittassāti"
msgstr "A mind without hindrances:"

#. </span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.40"
msgid "rāgā cittaṃ vinīvaraṇatā,"
msgstr "a mind without sensual desire,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.41"
msgid "dosā cittaṃ vinīvaraṇatā,"
msgstr "a mind without ill-will,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs4.1.42"
msgid "mohā cittaṃ vinīvaraṇatā."
msgstr "a mind without confusion."

#. </span>
