msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.8"
msgid "vasī …"
msgstr "masters …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.9"
msgid ""
"tena bhikkhunā suññāgāre catutthaṃ jhānaṃ sacchikatanti sampajānamusā "
"bhaṇantassa paṭi­vijānan­tassa āpatti thullaccayassa;"
msgstr ""
"has realized the fourth absorption in an empty dwelling,” then, if the "
"listener understands, he commits a serious offense when three conditions are "
"fulfilled;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.10"
msgid "na paṭi­vijānan­tassa āpatti dukkaṭassa … pe …"
msgstr ""
"if the listener does not understand, he commits an offense of wrong conduct "
"when three conditions are fulfilled … when seven conditions are fulfilled …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.11"
msgid "vinidhāya bhāvaṃ."
msgstr "he misrepresents his sentiment of what is true."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="168"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.701"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.12"
msgid "Tīhākārehi … pe … sattahākārehi yena te vihāro paribhutto …"
msgstr ""
"If he lies in full awareness, saying, “The monk who has made use of your "
"dwelling …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.13"
msgid "yena te cīvaraṃ paribhuttaṃ …"
msgstr "who has made use of your robe-cloth …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.14"
msgid "yena te piṇḍapāto paribhutto …"
msgstr "who has made use of your almsfood …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.15"
msgid "yena te senāsanaṃ paribhuttaṃ …"
msgstr "who has made use of your dwelling …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.16"
msgid "yena te gilā­nappac­caya­bhesaj­ja­parik­khāro paribhutto …"
msgstr "who has made use of your medicines"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.17"
msgid "so bhikkhu suññāgāre catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji …"
msgstr "attained the fourth absorption in an empty dwelling …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.18"
msgid "samāpajjati …"
msgstr "is attaining …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.19"
msgid "samāpanno …"
msgstr "has attained …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.20"
msgid "so bhikkhu suññāgāre catutthassa jhānassa lābhī …"
msgstr "obtains …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.21"
msgid "vasī …"
msgstr "masters …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.22"
msgid ""
"tena bhikkhunā suññāgāre catutthaṃ jhānaṃ sacchikatanti sampajānamusā "
"bhaṇantassa paṭi­vijānan­tassa āpatti thullaccayassa;"
msgstr ""
"has realized the fourth absorption in an empty dwelling,” then, if the "
"listener understands, he commits a serious offense when three conditions are "
"fulfilled;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.23"
msgid "na paṭi­vijānan­tassa āpatti dukkaṭassa … pe …"
msgstr ""
"if the listener does not understand, he commits an offense of wrong conduct "
"when three conditions are fulfilled … when seven conditions are fulfilled …"

#. The Pali has an additional set of ellipses points between “who has made use of your medicines” and “attained the fourth absorption in an empty dwelling.” This seems to be a mistake.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.24"
msgid "vinidhāya bhāvaṃ."
msgstr "he misrepresents his sentiment of what is true."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="169"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.702"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.25"
msgid "Tīhākārehi … pe … sattahākārehi yaṃ tvaṃ āgamma vihāraṃ adāsi …"
msgstr ""
"If he lies in full awareness, saying, “The monk to whom you gave a dwelling …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.26"
msgid "cīvaraṃ adāsi …"
msgstr "to whom you gave robe-cloth …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.27"
msgid "piṇḍapātaṃ adāsi …"
msgstr "to whom you gave almsfood …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.28"
msgid "senāsanaṃ adāsi …"
msgstr "to whom you gave a dwelling …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.29"
msgid ""
"gilā­nappac­caya­bhesaj­ja­parik­khā­raṃ adāsi so bhikkhu suññāgāre "
"catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji …"
msgstr ""
"to whom you gave medicines he attained the fourth absorption in an empty "
"dwelling …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.30"
msgid "samāpajjati …"
msgstr "is attaining …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.31"
msgid "samāpanno …"
msgstr "has attained …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.32"
msgid "so bhikkhu suññāgāre catutthassa jhānassa lābhī …"
msgstr "obtains …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.33"
msgid "vasī …"
msgstr "masters …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.34"
msgid ""
"tena bhikkhunā suññāgāre catutthaṃ jhānaṃ sacchikatanti sampajānamusā "
"bhaṇantassa paṭi­vijānan­tassa āpatti thullaccayassa;"
msgstr ""
"has realized the fourth absorption in an empty dwelling,” then, if the "
"listener understands, he commits a serious offense when three conditions are "
"fulfilled;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.100"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.35"
msgid "na paṭi­vijānan­tassa āpatti dukkaṭassa—"
msgstr ""
"if the listener does not understand, he commits an offense of wrong conduct "
"when three conditions are fulfilled … when seven conditions are fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.36"
msgid "pubbevassa hoti musā bhaṇissanti,"
msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.37"
msgid "bhaṇantassa hoti musā bhaṇāmīti,"
msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.38"
msgid "bhaṇitassa hoti musā mayā bhaṇitanti,"
msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.39"
msgid "vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ,"
msgstr "he misrepresents his view of what is true;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.40"
msgid "vinidhāya khantiṃ,"
msgstr "he misrepresents his belief of what is true;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.41"
msgid "vinidhāya ruciṃ,"
msgstr "he misrepresents his acceptance of what is true;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.42"
msgid "vinidhāya bhāvaṃ."
msgstr "he misrepresents his sentiment of what is true."

#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="170"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.703"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.43"
msgid "Peyyā­la­panna­rasa­kaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr "The successive fifteen are finished."

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.44"
msgid "Pac­ca­yap­paṭi­saṃ­yutta­vāraka­thā niṭṭhitā."
msgstr ""
"The exposition of the section on that connected with requisites is finished."

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs6.2.45"
msgid "Uttari­manus­sa­dhamma­cakka­peyyā­laṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr "The successive permutation series on superhuman qualities is finished."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="171"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pj.4.7"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.704"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.2"
msgid "adhimānena,"
msgstr "if he overestimates himself;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.3"
msgid "anul­lapa­nādhip­pāyassa,"
msgstr "if he does not intend to make a claim;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.4"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.5"
msgid "khittacittassa,"
msgstr "if he is deranged;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.6"
msgid "vedanāṭṭassa,"
msgstr "if he is overwhelmed by pain;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.7"
msgid "ādi­kammi­kas­sāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.7a"
msgid "4.1. Vinīta­vatthu­uddāna­gāthā"
msgstr "Case rulings"

#. </h2><div class="uddana"><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.7b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Mnemonic list"

#. </h5><p><a class="sc" id="172"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.705"></a> 
#. VAR: Adhimāne → adhimānena (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.8"
msgid "Adhimāne araññamhi,"
msgstr "About overestimation, in the wilderness,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.9"
msgid "piṇ­ḍo­paj­jhāriyā­patho;"
msgstr "Almsfood, a preceptor, behavior;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.10"
msgid "Saṃyojanā rahodhammā,"
msgstr "Fetters, qualities in private,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.11"
msgid "vihāro paccupaṭṭhito."
msgstr "A dwelling, attended on."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="173"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.706"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.12"
msgid "Na dukkaraṃ viriyamathopi maccuno,"
msgstr "Not difficult, energy, fear of death,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.13"
msgid "Bhāyāvuso vippaṭisāri sammā;"
msgstr "Remorseful friend, rightly;"

#. <br><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.172"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.14"
msgid "Viriyena yogena ārādhanāya,"
msgstr "By energy, by exertion,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.15"
msgid "Atha vedanāya adhivāsanā duve."
msgstr "Two on the enduring of feeling."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="174"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.707"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.16"
msgid "Brāhmaṇe pañca vatthūni,"
msgstr "Five stories on a brahmin,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.17"
msgid "aññaṃ byākaraṇā tayo;"
msgstr "Three on declaring final knowledge;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.19"
msgid "Agārāvaraṇā kāmā,"
msgstr "House, rejected sense-pleasures,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.20"
msgid "rati cāpi apakkami."
msgstr "And delight, set out."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="175"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.708"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.21"
msgid "Aṭṭhi pesi ubho gāvaghātakā,"
msgstr "Bone, lump: both are cattle-butchers,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.22"
msgid "Piṇḍo sākuṇiko nicchavi orabbhi;"
msgstr "A morsel is a poultry-butcher, a sheep-butcher is flayed;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.23"
msgid "Asi ca sūkariko satti māgavi,"
msgstr "And a pig-butcher and sword, a deer-hunter and knife,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.24"
msgid "Usu ca kāraṇiko sūci sārathi."
msgstr "And a torturer and arrow, a horse trainer and needle."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="176"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.709"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.25"
msgid "Yo ca sibbīyati sūcako hi so,"
msgstr "And a slanderer is sewn,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.26"
msgid "Aṇḍabhāri ahu gāmakūṭako;"
msgstr "A corrupt magistrate with testicles as burden;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.27"
msgid "Kūpe nimuggo hi so pāradāriko,"
msgstr "An adulterer submerged in a pit,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.28"
msgid "Gūthakhādī ahu duṭṭhabrāhmaṇo."
msgstr "An eater of dung was a wicked brahmin."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="177"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.710"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.29"
msgid "Nicchavitthī aticārinī ahu,"
msgstr "A flayed woman was an adulteress,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.28"
msgid "Maṅgulitthī ahu ikkhaṇitthikā;"
msgstr "An ugly woman was a fortune-teller;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.27"
msgid "Okilinī hi sapat­taṅ­gā­rokiri,"
msgstr "A sweltering woman scattered coals on a co-wife,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.28"
msgid "Sīsacchinno ahu coraghātako."
msgstr "A beheaded man was an executioner."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="178"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.711"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.29"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhunī sikkhamānā,"
msgstr "A monk, a nun, a trainee nun,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.30"
msgid "Sāmaṇero atha sāmaṇerikā;"
msgstr "A novice monk, then a novice nun;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.31"
msgid "Kassapassa vinayasmiṃ pabbajaṃ,"
msgstr "These having gone forth in the training of Kassapa"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.32"
msgid "Pāpakam­ma­makariṃsu tāvade."
msgstr "Did bad deeds just then."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="179"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.712"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.33"
msgid "Tapodā rājagahe yuddhaṃ,"
msgstr "The Tapodā in Rājagaha, battle,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.34"
msgid "nāgānogāhanena ca;"
msgstr "And with the plunging in of elephants;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.35"
msgid "Sobhito arahaṃ bhikkhu,"
msgstr "The perfected monk Sobhita"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs7.36"
msgid "pañca­kap­pasataṃ sareti."
msgstr "Recalls five hundred eons."

#. </p></div><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.1.0a"
msgid "4.2. Vinītavatthu"
msgstr "Case details, part 1"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="180"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pj.4.8"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pj.4.8.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.173"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.713"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.1.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu adhimānena aññaṃ byākāsi."
msgstr "At one time a monk declared final knowledge because of overestimation."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.1.2"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi—"
msgstr "He became remorseful, thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.1.3"
msgid "“bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ."
msgstr "“The Master has laid down a training rule."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.1.4"
msgid "Kacci nu kho ahaṃ pārājikaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno”ti?"
msgstr "Could it be that I’ve committed an offense entailing expulsion?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.1.5"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "He told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.1.6"
msgid "“Anāpatti, bhikkhu, adhimānenā”ti."
msgstr "“There’s no offense for one who overestimates himself.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.1.7"
msgid "(1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="181"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pj.4.8.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.714"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.101"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu paṇidhāya araññe viharati—"
msgstr "At one time a monk lived in the wilderness"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.2"
msgid "“evaṃ maṃ jano sambhāvessatī”ti."
msgstr "because he wanted people to esteem him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.3"
msgid "Taṃ jano sambhāvesi."
msgstr "People esteemed him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.4"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "He became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.5"
msgid "“anāpatti, bhikkhu, pārājikassa."
msgstr "“There’s no offense entailing expulsion."

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.6"
msgid "Na ca, bhikkhave, paṇidhāya araññe vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "But, monks, you should not live in the wilderness because of a wish."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.7"
msgid "Yo vaseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti."
msgstr "If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.8"
msgid "(2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="182"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.715"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.9"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu paṇidhāya piṇḍāya carati—"
msgstr "At one time a monk was walking for almsfood"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.10"
msgid "“evaṃ maṃ jano sambhāvessatī”ti."
msgstr "because he wanted people to esteem him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.11"
msgid "Taṃ jano sambhāvesi."
msgstr "People esteemed him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.12"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "He became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.13"
msgid "“anāpatti, bhikkhu, pārājikassa."
msgstr "“There’s no offense entailing expulsion."

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.14"
msgid "Na ca, bhikkhave, paṇidhāya piṇḍāya caritabbaṃ."
msgstr "But, monks, you should not walk for almsfood because of a wish."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.15"
msgid "Yo careyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti."
msgstr "If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.2.16"
msgid "(3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="183"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pj.4.8.3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.716"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "At one time a monk said to another monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.3.2"
msgid "“ye, āvuso, amhākaṃ upajjhāyassa saddhivihārikā sabbeva arahanto”ti."
msgstr "“Those who are pupils of our preceptor are all perfected ones.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.3.3"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "He became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.3.4"
msgid "“kiṃcitto tvaṃ, bhikkhū”ti?"
msgstr "“What was your intention, monk?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:pts-cs8.3.5"
msgid "“Ullapa­nā­dhip­pāyo ahaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“I wanted to make a claim, Master.”"

